nodes.title: Workflow quick guide
widgets_values:
# Workflow quick guide

## Models
You will need both Qwen Image and Flux 1 Krea models.  The first will generate the base image, having better prompt adherence and great detailed output.  The second will add realistic details to people skin, eyes and hair.
1. [Qwen Image model](https://docs.comfy.org/tutorials/image/qwen/qwen-image#1-workflow-file)
2. [Flux 1 Krea Dev model](https://docs.comfy.org/tutorials/flux/flux1-krea-dev#2-manual-model-installation)
3. Any SD 1.5, SDXL or Illustrious model. I use [Illustrious Realism by klaabu](https://civitai.com/models/1412827/illustrious-realism-by-klaabu)

## The workflow
Qwen model is extremely good at following your prompt, but it lacks details and quality for photo realistic images.  This is why I added a second pass with Flux Krea or a SD 1.5/SDXL/Illustrious model of you choice and an upscale module that uses the 2nd pass model you chose and [UltraSharpV2](https://huggingface.co/Tenofas/ComfyUI/resolve/main/upscale_models/4x-UltraSharpV2.safetensors?download=true) as upscale model.  Negative prompt is not necessary, and it would only affect Qwen Image generation if you use a CFG higher than 1.00 or in the 2nd pass if you use a SD1.5/SDXL/Illustrious model.   
You can choose to apply or bypass the Upscaler module and the Save Image module.

Use key "1" and "2" to navigate the Workflow.

Default is 3.10
Increase the value of shift in you get blurry/dark images.
Decrease the value if you want to increase the detail of the image.

nodes.title: Ksampler settings
widgets_values:
# Qwen KSampler settings

## Steps
Even if the official page suggest to use 50 steps, you can reach good results even with just 10 steps.  I suggest to stay around 25-30 steps.

## CFG
If you want to speed up the workflow, do not use negative prompts and set the CFG to 1.0.  Default is at 4.0, I use 2.5-3.0.

## Sampler - Scheduler
I suggest to use dpmpp_2m + sgm_uniform, but you can play with settings here!
